# Copy this file to .env (gitignored) and fill in real values.
#
# These comments are living documentation: each token's block spells out the
# exact permissions and creation steps so it can be regenerated from scratch.
# Any change to a token's required scope (e.g. adding D1) must update the
# comment here in the same commit.
#
# Loading: wrangler reads .env natively; everything else gets these vars
# injected by mise via `[env] _.file = ".env"` in mise.toml.
# Worker *runtime* secrets do NOT go here — they go in .dev.vars locally and
# `npx wrangler secret put` in production.
#
# GitHub auth deliberately has no token here: local sessions push over SSH and
# use the gh keyring login; Claude Code web/Dispatch sessions get repo-scoped
# credentials from the Claude GitHub App; CI would use the built-in
# GITHUB_TOKEN. If a constrained local-agent flow is ever needed, add a
# fine-grained PAT (repo couetilc/news; Metadata read, Contents read/write,
# Pull requests read/write) as GH_TOKEN and switch the git remote to HTTPS.

# ── CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Purpose: lets wrangler deploy the Worker non-interactively (local machines
# with a `wrangler login` OAuth session don't need it).
# Where this token lives (keep all copies in sync when rotating):
#   1. This file's sibling .env on Connor's machine (local + Dispatch deploys)
#   2. GitHub Actions repo secret CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN on couetilc/news
#      (canonical deploy path: merge to main → CI deploys). Rotate with:
#      grep '^CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=' .env | cut -d= -f2- | gh secret set CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
#   NOT in the claude.ai cloud environment — it is deliberately credential-free
#   (cloud sessions test + push branches; CI deploys). See
#   .claude/skills/agentic-environments/SKILL.md.
# Regenerate at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
#   → Create Token → template "Edit Cloudflare Workers", scoped as below.
# Actual grants of the current token (created 2026-06-10):
#   Account ("Connor@couetil.com's Account", id dbaa50e60c18b19d483578c42d9bb3ee):
#     • Workers Scripts: Edit               (required: deploy code, versions, secrets)
#     • Workers KV Storage: Edit            (required: SESSION KV auto-provisioned on deploy)
#     • Workers R2 Storage: Edit            (granted ahead of need: future R2 buckets)
#     • Workers Observability: Edit         (observability is enabled in wrangler.jsonc)
#     • Workers Tail: Read                  (npx wrangler tail)
#     • Workers Builds Configuration: Edit  (Workers Builds CI; unused today)
#     • Workers Agents Configuration: Edit  (unused today)
#     • Cloudflare Pages: Edit              (unused — this project deploys Workers, not Pages)
#     • Containers: Edit                    (unused today)
#     • Account Settings: Read              (account discovery/verification)
#   Zone (only cuteteal.com, id 1413a4570fa6e193d5f224ebb5220bb5):
#     • Workers Routes: Edit                (required: custom domain news.cuteteal.com)
#   All users:
#     • User Details: Read, Memberships: Read  (wrangler whoami / account listing)
#   Still NOT granted (add to the token + update this block when the resource
#   is declared in wrangler.jsonc): D1: Edit.
#   Fallback: if custom-domain attach fails on permissions, add Zone → DNS: Edit.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
